// WARRANT#33 (forge-edge 2, r1 -- "Cell identity + Sufficiency + shrinkage-prior wiring",
// 2026-07-16, first warrant of the tungsten-smithing era): purely additive scaffolding on the
// existing LivingEdgeCell layer. Adds a formal, named LE_TRADE_MIN_N=500 trading-weight floor
// (Prohibition #5, previously only referenced in comments/inline literals) plus LE_IsTradeable(),
// and empirical-Bayes shrinkage-toward-parent helpers (LE_ShrunkMean/LE_ShrunkMeanDemeaned) that
// pull thin cells toward g_LE_GlobalMeanFwd (the one global parent this codebase already
// computes) with a fixed prior strength (LE_DIAG_MIN_N=30 virtual samples) -- a real, principled,
// but simpler construction than a full regime-specific parent hierarchy, flagged as such, not
// oversold (same pattern as WARRANT#28's soft-membership). Nothing here is read by
// ComputeEntryConviction, sizing, or any live gate yet -- that wiring is forge-edge 2's own r6
// ("Bayesian live-cell core"), a separate, later, still-gated warrant. See forge-edge-2/SKILL.md.
// WARRANT#34 (forge-indicate, r1 -- "Relationship scaffolding + Sufficiency wiring", 2026-07-16,
// second warrant of the tungsten-smithing era): purely additive scaffolding for the signal-
// formation agent. Defines a bounded 6-pair subset (deliberately not the full C(6,2)=15
// combinations over g_RegimeIC's 6 CEUS components -- forge-indicate's own thesis rejects a full
// confirm/conflict graph as too costly; bounded pairwise captures most of the value) and the
// per-pair, per-regime RelationshipCell cache r2 ("3F Relationship measurement") will populate.
// No measurement logic yet -- RI_CoherenceIndex() reads only whatever is already in the cache and
// returns a neutral 0.5 when nothing is sufficient, matching LivingEdgeCell's own fail-open
// convention. Nothing here is read by ComputeEntryConviction, IC, weights, or the threshold yet --
// see forge-indicate/SKILL.md sections 3, 5, and 7.
