// orphaned-but-compiled diagnostics (LE_ComputePosteriorEdge/CappedKellySize since WARRANT#44,
// Keys3_EpisodeState/EpisodeDwell/StructureSequence since WARRANT#65/70/71) into the existing
// Forge_ReportGhostValidation call site, including the real forge-indicate->forge-edge-2
// composition (RI_CoherenceIndex feeding LE_ComputeLiveCellDecision). Read-only, no gating change.
// WARRANT#73 (keys-3, 2026-07-19, item 18): scale-selection diagnostic -- R at bar 100 across 4
// candidate lookback scales (50/100/200/400 bars), logged side by side. Measurement only.
// WARRANT#74 (forge-indicate, 2026-07-19, r7 continuation): Sigma-convergence status report --
// composes reliability (WARRANT#68) + relationship coherence (RI_CoherenceIndex) + an illustrative
// RI_ThresholdWithHysteresis (WARRANT#42) sample into one status line. Read-only, no gating change.
// WARRANT#75 (forge-parallel, 2026-07-19, real PBO -- CAREFULLY, PRECISELY, per Manuel's explicit
// go-ahead after the prior session's deferral): a simplified, single-split PBO-style estimate,
// sampled every 500th draw (~100 samples, not all 50,000) inside Stage 6's existing global-random
// search -- reuses values (rWR, valWR) Stage 6 already computes for its own acceptance check, adds
// only an O(1) array write on already-surviving iterations, zero new bar-scanning. Post-loop
// ranking runs once on <=100 numbers (negligible). NOT touched: the loop's Sleep(1) cadence, its
// timing profile, its accept/reject control flow, or any existing line. Feeds ForgeScorecard.pbo
// (worst-of-9-regimes) for the first time with a real, if approximate, number -- explicitly NOT
// the full Bailey & Lopez de Prado CSCV method, flagged as such everywhere it's logged.
// WARRANT#76 (forge-parallel, 2026-07-19, calibration budget): MaxCalibrationMinutes default
// raised 90 -> 240 ("budget shouldn't ever be an issue") -- real evidence it was tight (2026-07-17
// live run logged multiple budget-tight warnings), every phase already fails open on timeout, so
// this only ever buys more time before that same safe fallback, never a new failure mode.
// WARRANT#77 (forge-indicate, 2026-07-19, r7 "relationship-OOS"): buckets ghost trades by their
// regime's current RI_CoherenceIndex into low/mid/high bands, logs realized WR per band -- the
// decisive test of whether relationship coherence predicts outcome, same pattern as Keys-3's
// WARRANT#64. Diagnostic only.
// WARRANT#78 (system coherence pass, 2026-07-19): found and fixed two real seam breaks. (1)
// WARRANT#64's R-band bucketing used HARDCODED 0.35/0.65 literals, independent of WARRANT#65/70's
// named KEYS3_R_HIGH/KEYS3_R_LOW constants of the same value -- moved the #define earlier (single
// canonical source before Forge_ReportGhostValidation), updated WARRANT#64 to reference it. (2)
// g_RegimePBOEstimate (WARRANT#75) had no reset point -- a stale estimate from a PRIOR calibration
// cycle could silently leak into a fresh run's ForgeScorecard if that regime's Stage 6 re-sampling
// didn't reach 20 samples the second time. Fixed by invalidating only THIS regime's own slot at
// the top of OptimizeComponentWeightsForRegime -- deliberately not a blanket 9-regime reset, since
// Phase 3B's outer loop supports checkpoint/resume and that would wipe out valid estimates from
// regimes already completed earlier in the same resumed run.
// WARRANT#79 (forge-parallel, 2026-07-19, FULL CSCV): the genuine Bailey & Lopez de Prado (2014)
// PBO algorithm, per Manuel's explicit "more strategic rigor isn't a problem" go-ahead --
// supersedes WARRANT#75's single-split proxy where data supports it. Independent CSCV_N=200-
// candidate x CSCV_S=8-block search, completely separate from Stage 6's own 50,000-draw loop
// (shares no state, no RNG seed, no control flow). Combinatorial rank/logit statistic computed
// over C(8,4)=70 balanced splits. Cheaper in total bar-touches than the Stage-6 search it audits.
// WARRANT#80 (forge-cleanup-3 lineage, 2026-07-22, "maximize real calibration stats" standing
// directive): ValidateWeightsAgainstFinalBrackets (WARRANT#56) already measures, per regime, WR
// under BOTH the fixed default bracket (Phase 3B's own trainingWR, 1.5/2.5 ATR) and the real
// calibrated final bracket (Phase 3C's SL/TP mult) -- but when the final bracket scores worse, the
// function only regularized the WEIGHTS toward equal-blend and left the (already-shown-worse)
// calibrated bracket in place for live trading. That discarded a comparison it had already made:
// the fixed default bracket, right there in the same log line, was the empirically better choice.
// Gated OFF by default (input EnableBracketFallbackOnRecheck) -- this changes which SL/TP mult a
// regime actually trades with, a materially higher-stakes decision than a weight blend, so it ships
// as real, wired, dormant scaffolding rather than always-on, same risk-tiering this campaign has
// used since WARRANT#27/#28. See ValidateWeightsAgainstFinalBrackets for the guarded logic.
// WARRANT#81 (forge-indicate, 2026-07-22, r5 remainder "3H threshold-to-target"): WARRANT#42 built
// only the hysteresis third of 3H; WARRANT#68's reliability curve (g_ConvictionBins[10]) was never
// queried to answer 3H's actual question -- what predicted-probability cutoff would hit a given win-
// rate target. Added RI_ThresholdForTargetWR(), pure read over already-computed bins, surfaced in
// Forge_ReportReliabilityCurve as a diagnostic line. Not wired into any live threshold decision.
// WARRANT#82 (forge-parallel lane, 2026-07-22): g_ForgeChampion/g_ForgeChampionSet (the ratchet's
// entire memory of what the current best scorecard is) were never persisted anywhere -- confirmed
// by grep, no FileWrite/FileRead site existed for either. Every restart silently forgot the
// champion, so ForgeRatchetPromote's own "no champion seeded yet -- first scorecard becomes
// champion by definition" branch fired on every cold start, defeating the entire monotonic-ratchet
// guarantee across restarts (a worse post-restart challenger could freely become the new "champion"
// with nothing to be non-inferior to). Fixed with a guarded-tail persistence, same precedent as
// WARRANT#57/62, placed as the new last tail in SaveSystemState/LoadSystemState.
// WARRANT#83 (forge-edge-2/forge-parallel r8, "reversion checkpoint" storage half, 2026-07-22):
// ForgeChampion_Seed now stashes the outgoing champion into a single-slot g_ForgeChampionPrev
// before overwriting; ForgeChampion_Revert() can restore it. The auto-trigger for WHEN to call
// Revert (a real judgment call -- what counts as "regressed in live use") is deliberately NOT
// invented here; this warrant only builds the storage + manual-revert mechanism so a future warrant
// can wire a real trigger once Manuel defines one. Champion tail schema bumped to v2 to carry the
// stash; a v1 file (never actually written by any completed run yet) is skipped cleanly, not
// partially misread.
// WARRANT#84 (keys-3 item 15 remainder, "dissipation exit wired", 2026-07-22): WARRANT#65/70 built
// the episode-state classifier and dwell measurement, both left uncalled. Added
// ShouldExitOnDissipation() (per-bar cached, see cost-audit comment at its definition) and wired it
// into ManageIndividualTradeAdvanced, gated HARD OFF by default (EnableDissipationExit) -- closing
// an open trade is a live-decision change, same risk tier as WARRANT#27/28/80.
// WARRANT#85 (forge-indicate Pillar C "shrinkage-to-prior", 2026-07-22): RI_PairwiseLift's hard
// cliff (0.0 below RI_DIAG_MIN_N) is a real sentinel other code depends on -- added
// RI_PairwiseLiftShrunk() as a NEW parallel function (existing sentinel untouched) applying
// WARRANT#33's own empirical-Bayes shrinkage formula/prior-strength convention to each side of the
// lift computation independently. Diagnostic only, surfaced in RI_LogRelationshipReport.
// Manuel: "finish everything stalled to be wired into the rest of logics, improve edge detection
// given sign-switching, every phase elite, maximum capability per existing." Four warrants shipped
// in response, 2026-07-22:
// WARRANT#86 (edge detection given sign-switching): ComputeLivingEdgeInversionTrim (always-on,
// bounded, reduce-only) now ALSO trims on Keys-3 episode-dissipation (reuses WARRANT#84's cached
// computation, zero new cost) alongside its existing per-cell TRANSITIONING check -- a genuinely
// orthogonal, market-wide sign-instability signal fused with the existing per-cell one.
// WARRANT#87: ProbDB_AnnotateAll (built WARRANT#43, never called) now runs for real after every
// successful Phase 4 build -- read-only w.r.t. ProbDB itself, zero live-decision risk.
// WARRANT#88: RI_LogisticSquash (built WARRANT#40, never called) surfaced as a new diagnostic line
// in the Sigma-convergence report -- NOT applied to the live score (would be a system-wide
// live-decision change far beyond this warrant's scope).
// WARRANT#89: LE_OptimalStoppingExit (built WARRANT#46, never called) wired as a new gated
// (default OFF) exit check, same risk tier as WARRANT#84/28 -- closing a trade needs consent.
// Deliberately did NOT flip any of the 4 existing gated live-decision flags to true, and did not
// invent new ones defaulting true -- "maximum capability per existing" is read as "use everything
// already built to its fullest SAFE extent," not as license to skip the consent this campaign has
// required for every live-decision change since WARRANT#27.
// WARRANT#90 (2026-07-22): Manuel replied "go for it" to that exact question -- all 5 gated
// live-decision flags flipped true: EnableSignAgnosticEntries (WARRANT#27), UseSoftMembershipFitting
// (WARRANT#28), EnableOptimalStoppingExit (WARRANT#89), EnableDissipationExit (WARRANT#84),
// EnableBracketFallbackOnRecheck (WARRANT#80). ONLY these 5 lines changed value -- every other
// input, every trim/gate threshold, every function body untouched. This is the first time ANY of
// these 5 mechanisms will actually fire on a real run; none has been live-validated before now, and
// with all 5 active simultaneously a first live run won't cleanly isolate which one did what if
// something looks off -- flagged plainly, not hidden.
#define EA_VERSION "10.06"
// LESSON#4 (forge pass 2): every runtime Print/PrintFormat/LogCriticalEvent version banner
// hardcoded the literal "SLS(24)" independent of the file's actual identity -- confirmed live
// on 2026-07-09 when a genuinely-recompiled SLS(29).ex4 still printed "SLS(24)" throughout a
// full calibration run. EA_BUILD_ID is now the single place this identity is derived; bump
// this one line each pass instead of hand-editing every Print site again.
// WARRANT#20 (forge pass, 2026-07-10; renumbered from a same-day #17 collision with the
// ledger's real WARRANT#17 -- ATM's Point*N fix, pass 6 -- caught in the 2026-07-11 polish
// pass): RunIndicatorIntelligence()/RunFeatureSignalDiagnostic() -- the pre-Phase-1 INDINTEL
// mining pass -- scan the full ~65k-bar history with no TLog visibility and no time budget
// short of the full 90-min MaxCalibrationMinutes ceiling. Confirmed live: TUNGSTEN_live.log
// stayed at 0 bytes for 9+ minutes of real, climbing-CPU work with zero disk evidence of
// progress -- indistinguishable from a hang. Fix: TLog entry/exit markers on both functions,
// plus a dedicated ~90s local budget (independent of CalibrationTimedOut()) so this pass can
// never again silently consume unlimited time.
// WARRANT#19 (forge pass, 2026-07-10, indicator sync): audited all 9 custom indicators against
// their TUNGSTEN integration (IE_ReadAtBar). 8/9 already expose a continuous, ATR/percentile-
// legal signed reading and were left untouched (no rewrite for its own sake). VRC was a
// structurally dead channel -- out[IE_VRC] was hardcoded to 0.0 in both the live and
// calibration read paths, per its "DIRECTIONLESS by design" comment. That made VRC contribute
// exactly zero to BOTH the directional IC (Stage 1) and the amplitude IC (Stage 2) in
// RunIndicatorIntelligence -- a real, measurable signal (VRC's own composite vol ratio, buf1,
// already ATR/self-baseline relative -- legal Form 2) was being thrown away unread. Fix: read
// buf1 and expose (composite-1.0) clamped as the reading. This does NOT assert a directional
// claim -- it hands the IC pipeline a real, legal, previously-unmeasured magnitude signal and
// lets significance shrinkage decide, per doctrine, whether it earns any weight at all.
// WARRANT#21 (forge polish pass, 2026-07-11): see SPG_SessionWindow() near IE_Update() for
// full reasoning -- SPG's session-probability window was hardcoded NY hours for every symbol
// including JPY/AUD/NZD crosses, which live in Asia session per this project's own doctrine.
// Also this pass: fixed a same-day WARRANT#17/#17 numbering collision (see WARRANT#20 above),
// re-reviewed the 3 changes shipped in SLS(35)/SLS(36) (wraparound-safe, dimensionally sound,
// no bugs found), swept for remaining illegal Point*N sites (0 found -- all 18 occurrences are
// legitimate degenerate-guards, doctrine's "8 sites remain" note is now stale/resolved), and
// verified SL-multiplier fallback parity (1.3 default consistent across both consumer sites).
// Flagged, not fixed: CATREC's regime-preservation gate (~line 46322) sets a live rebuild/
// preserve blend factor from as few as 5 trades -- structurally similar to the recurring
// underpowered-gate defect class, but CATREC is a live catastrophic-recovery mechanism that
// may deliberately trade statistical rigor for reaction speed; needs Manuel's judgment on
// intent before touching, not a static-analysis call.
#define EA_BUILD_ID "SLS(92)"
#define DEFAULT_REGIME_THRESHOLD 55.0


//| TYPE DEFINITIONS - Must come before ANY usage                    |

// Pattern Type Enumeration
enum PatternType {
    PATTERN_UNKNOWN = 0,

    // --- REGIME 0: STRONG BULLISH TREND PATTERNS ---
    // Bull Flag: Impulse up, tight descending channel pullback, break up
    // Candle signature: 3-5 large bull candles, then 3-7 small candles
    // declining slightly, then breakout above channel
    PATTERN_BULL_FLAG = 1,

    // Ascending Triangle: Rising lows meeting flat resistance
    // Candle signature: each pullback low is higher, resistance rejections flatten
    // Body-to-range ratio on pullbacks < 0.4, breakout bar ratio > 0.6
    PATTERN_ASCENDING_TRIANGLE = 2,

    // Cup and Handle: Rounded recovery then tight consolidation before continuation
    // Candle signature: U-shape decline+recovery (10-30 bars), then 3-7 bar drift
    // RSI recovers from oversold during cup, stays 45-60 during handle
    PATTERN_CUP_AND_HANDLE = 3,

    // Momentum Continuation: BOS retest, small pullback, higher high
    // Candle signature: break candle body > 60% of range, retest within 3 bars,
    // continuation bar closes above the break level
    PATTERN_MOMENTUM_CONTINUATION = 4,

    // Bullish Pennant: Converging trendlines after sharp impulse
    // Candle signature: 2-4 bar impulse, 4-8 bar pennant with shrinking ATR,
    // breakout on expanding volume
    PATTERN_BULLISH_PENNANT = 5,

    // --- REGIME 1: STRONG BEARISH TREND PATTERNS ---
    // Bear Flag: Impulse down, tight ascending channel pullback, break down
    // Candle signature: 3-5 large bear candles, then 3-7 small rising candles,
    // then breakdown below channel
    PATTERN_BEAR_FLAG = 6,

    // Descending Triangle: Falling highs meeting flat support
    // Candle signature: each rally high is lower, support tests flatten
    // Body-to-range on rallies < 0.4, breakdown bar ratio > 0.6
    PATTERN_DESCENDING_TRIANGLE = 7,

    // Inverted Cup and Handle: Rounded top then tight consolidation before decline
    // Candle signature: inverted U-shape (10-30 bars), then 3-7 bar drift up,
    // RSI fades from overbought during cup, stays 40-55 during handle
    PATTERN_INVERTED_CUP_HANDLE = 8,

    // Bearish Momentum Continuation: BOS retest, small bounce, lower low
    // Candle signature: break candle body > 60% of range downward, bounce within
    // 3 bars, continuation bar closes below the break level
    PATTERN_BEARISH_CONTINUATION = 9,

    // Bearish Pennant: Converging trendlines after sharp drop
    PATTERN_BEARISH_PENNANT = 10,

    // --- REGIME 2: BULLISH REVERSAL PATTERNS ---
    PATTERN_DOUBLE_BOTTOM = 11,

    // Inverse Head and Shoulders: Three lows, middle lowest, neckline break
    // Candle signature: Left shoulder low, deeper head low, higher right shoulder,
    // each low shows rejection wick (ratio > 0.4), neckline break on volume
    PATTERN_INV_HEAD_SHOULDERS = 12,

    // Morning Star: Three candle reversal at low
    // Candle signature: Large bear candle (body > 60% range), small indecision
    // candle (body < 30% range, can be doji), large bull candle closing > 50%
    // into first candle's body
    PATTERN_MORNING_STAR = 13,

    // Hammer at Support: Single candle rejection from support
    // Candle signature: Lower wick >= 2x body size, body in top 30% of range,
    // occurs within 0.5 ATR of identified support level
    PATTERN_HAMMER_AT_SUPPORT = 14,

    // Bullish CHoCH: Change of character from bearish to bullish structure
    // Candle signature: After LL/LH sequence, price makes first HH breaking
    // last significant swing high, confirming bar closes above with body > 50% range
    PATTERN_BULLISH_CHOCH = 15,

    // Bullish Engulfing at Support: Bearish candle fully engulfed by bull
    // Candle signature: Bull candle open <= prior bear close, bull close >= prior
    // bear open, bull body > 120% of bear body, at or near support level
    PATTERN_BULLISH_ENGULFING = 16,

    // --- REGIME 3: BEARISH REVERSAL PATTERNS ---
    PATTERN_DOUBLE_TOP = 17,

    // Head and Shoulders: Three highs, middle highest, neckline break
    // Candle signature: Left shoulder high, higher head, lower right shoulder,
    // each high shows rejection wick (ratio > 0.4), neckline break on volume
    PATTERN_HEAD_SHOULDERS = 18,

    // Evening Star: Three candle reversal at high
    // Candle signature: Large bull candle (body > 60% range), small indecision
    // candle (body < 30% range), large bear candle closing > 50% into first
    // candle's body
    PATTERN_EVENING_STAR = 19,

    // Shooting Star at Resistance: Single candle rejection from resistance
    // Candle signature: Upper wick >= 2x body size, body in bottom 30% of range,
    // occurs within 0.5 ATR of identified resistance level
    PATTERN_SHOOTING_STAR_AT_RES = 20,

    // Bearish CHoCH: Change of character from bullish to bearish structure
    // Candle signature: After HH/HL sequence, price makes first LL breaking
    // last significant swing low, confirming bar closes below with body > 50% range
    PATTERN_BEARISH_CHOCH = 21,

    // Bearish Engulfing at Resistance: Bullish candle fully engulfed by bear
    // Candle signature: Bear candle open >= prior bull close, bear close <= prior
    // bull open, bear body > 120% of bull body, at or near resistance level
    PATTERN_BEARISH_ENGULFING = 22,

    // --- REGIME 4: CLEAN RANGE PATTERNS ---
    // Support/Resistance Bounce: Clean touch and reversal from range boundaries
    // Candle signature: Within 0.3 ATR of S or R, rejection wick ratio > 0.35,
    // 2-3 confirmation candles following through, range boundary tested 2+ times
    PATTERN_SR_BOUNCE = 23,

    // Range Compression (Inside Bar Cluster): Narrowing candles before bounce
    // Candle signature: 3+ consecutive inside bars (each within prior range),
    // ATR of cluster < 0.5x ATR of surrounding bars, resolves back to boundary
    PATTERN_RANGE_COMPRESSION = 24,

    // Failed Breakout (Fakeout): Price briefly breaks S/R then reverses hard
    // Candle signature: Candle closes beyond boundary by < 0.5 ATR, next candle
    // reverses and closes back inside range with body > 50% of breakout candle
    PATTERN_FAILED_BREAKOUT = 25,

    // --- REGIME 5: CHOPPY TRADEABLE RANGE ---
    // Wide S/R Respect: Oscillation between wider support and resistance
    // Candle signature: Multiple tests of both boundaries (2+ each), range width
    // > 1.5 ATR, price spends > 40% of time within middle 50% of range
    PATTERN_WIDE_SR_RESPECT = 26,

    // Range Fakeout Reversal: False break with momentum reversal
    // Candle signature: Break beyond boundary followed by rapid reversal,
    // reversal candle body covers > 70% of breakout candle within 2 bars,
    // volume on reversal > volume on breakout
    PATTERN_RANGE_FAKEOUT = 27,

    // Compression-Expansion Cycle: ATR contracting then expanding within range
    // Candle signature: 4-6 bars of shrinking range (ATR declining 20%+),
    // followed by expansion candle that respects range boundary (no close outside)
    PATTERN_COMPRESSION_EXPANSION = 28,

    // --- REGIME 6: NOISE (Detection only - do not trade) ---
    // Whipsaw: Rapid direction changes with no follow-through
    // Candle signature: 3+ direction changes in 5 bars, each move < 0.5 ATR,
    // no candle body > 40% of range
    PATTERN_WHIPSAW = 29,

    // --- REGIME 7: EXHAUSTION / DISTRIBUTION ---
    // Climax Volume Reversal: Massive volume spike at trend extreme
    // Candle signature: Volume > 2.5x 20-bar average, large body candle (> 65%
    // range) at highest/lowest point, followed by reversal or narrow-range bar
    PATTERN_CLIMAX_REVERSAL = 30,

    // Parabolic Stall: Price moving too fast, beginning to stall
    // Candle signature: Each successive candle body getting smaller while ATR
    // expands, RSI > 80 or < 20, last 2+ bars fail to make new extreme
    PATTERN_PARABOLIC_STALL = 31,

    // Divergence Setup: Price makes new extreme but momentum does not
    // Candle signature: Price HH or LL within 5 bars, RSI fails to confirm
    // (RSI at new extreme lower/higher than prior extreme), MACD histogram fading
    PATTERN_DIVERGENCE = 32,

    // Spinning Top at Extreme: Indecision after extended move
    // Candle signature: Body < 25% of range, upper and lower wicks approximately
    // equal (within 40% of each other), occurs after 10+ bar trend, ADX > 30
    PATTERN_SPINNING_TOP_EXTREME = 33,

    // Structural constants (kept for compatibility)
    PATTERN_HH = 34,
    PATTERN_HL = 35,
    PATTERN_LH = 36,
    PATTERN_LL = 37,
    PATTERN_CONSOLIDATION = 38,
    PATTERN_DOJI = 39,
    
    // Additional patterns for calibration
    PATTERN_BREAKOUT = 41,                      // Generic breakout pattern
    PATTERN_RANGE_EXPANSION_REVERSAL = 42,      // Range expansion followed by reversal
    PATTERN_RANGE_BOUND = 43,                   // Simple range-bound oscillation
    
    PATTERN_NONE = 44
};

// Swing point type enumeration
enum SwingType {
    SWING_NONE = 0,
    SWING_HIGH = 1,
    SWING_LOW = 2
};

struct SwingPoint {
    int barIndex;
    double price;
    SwingType type;
    datetime time;
    bool confirmed;
    bool isHigh;
    bool isBroken;
    datetime brokenTime;
    int strength;
};

struct MicroPattern {
    PatternType type;
    int startBar;
    int endBar;
    double confidence;
    datetime detectedAt;
    bool active;
    SwingPoint points[5];  // Up to 5 swing points
    int pointCount;
};

struct MacroPattern {
    PatternType type;
    int startBar;
    int endBar;
    double confidence;
    datetime detectedAt;
    bool active;
    SwingPoint points[10];  // Up to 10 swing points
    int pointCount;
    MicroPattern microSequence[10];  // Micro patterns that formed this macro
    int microCount;
};

struct MarketStateFeatures {
    // RAW PRICE DATA (FUNDAMENTAL)
    double open;
    double high;
    double low;
    double close;
    double spread;
    
    // Market Structure Features (PRIMARY)
    bool hasHigherHigh;
    bool hasHigherLow;
    bool hasLowerLow;
    bool hasLowerHigh;
    bool recentBOS;
    bool recentCHoCH;
    double structureClarity;
    double swingStrength;
    int swingsInLast20Bars;
    double avgSwingSize;
    
    // Shorthand aliases
    bool hasHH;
    bool hasHL;
    bool hasLL;
    bool hasLH;
    
    // Price Action Features
    double bodyToWickRatio;
    double trendConsistency;  // How many bars follow trend vs counter
    bool insideBar;
    bool engulfing;
    bool pinBar;
    double rejectionStrength; // Wick rejection size
    
    // Momentum & Flow Features  
    double vwap;           // daily VWAP
    bool   aboveVWAP;      // price above VWAP
    double adx;
    double atr;
    double atrPercent;
    double rsi;
    double rsiSlope;          // Is RSI rising or falling?
    double macdHistogram;
    double macdSlope;
    double macdCurrent;
    
    // Volume & Conviction
    double volumeRatio;
    double volumeTrend;       // Is volume increasing or decreasing?
    bool volumeSpike;
    
    // Range & Volatility Context
    double pricePosition;     // 0-1 where in recent range?
    double rangeCompression;  // Is range tightening? (accumulation sign)
    double volatilityTrend;   // Expanding or contracting?
    bool nearSupport;
    bool nearResistance;
    
    // Timing & Context
    int timeSession;
    int dayOfWeek;
    bool postNews;
    
    // ORDER BLOCK CONTEXT (Elite Trading - Institutional Zones)
    bool nearBullishOB;           // Bullish order block within 20 pips
    bool nearBearishOB;           // Bearish order block within 20 pips
    double obDistancePips;        // Distance to nearest OB
    int obAge;                    // Bars since OB formed (fresh vs tested)
    
    // FAIR VALUE GAP CONTEXT (Price Imbalances)
    bool insideBullishFVG;        // Currently in bullish FVG zone
    bool insideBearishFVG;        // Currently in bearish FVG zone
    bool fvgAheadUp;              // FVG above current price
    bool fvgAheadDown;            // FVG below current price
    double fvgDistancePips;       // Distance to nearest FVG
    
    // ADVANCED CANDLESTICK PATTERNS (Confirmation Signals)
    bool isDoji;                  // Indecision candle
    bool isHammer;                // Bullish rejection (long lower wick)
    bool isShootingStar;          // Bearish rejection (long upper wick)
    bool atKeyLevel;              // At support/resistance (confirms pattern)
    
    // E8 ENHANCEMENT: HISTORICAL CONTEXT FEATURES
    double priceChange20;         // % price change over 20 bars
    double priceChange50;         // % price change over 50 bars  
    double priceChange100;        // % price change over 100 bars
    int consecutiveUpBars;        // Consecutive up closes
    int consecutiveDownBars;      // Consecutive down closes
    int consecutiveUpSwings;      // Consecutive HH/HL patterns
    int consecutiveDownSwings;    // Consecutive LL/LH patterns
    double avgVolume50;           // Average volume over 50 bars
    double volumeRatioToAvg50;    // Current volume vs 50-bar average
    double atrChange50;           // ATR change over 50 bars
    double rsiChange20;           // RSI change over 20 bars
    int bullishBarsL20;           // Count of bullish bars in last 20
    int bearishBarsL20;           // Count of bearish bars in last 20
    int volatileBarsL20;          // Count of volatile bars in last 20
    double marketBias20;          // Overall bias -1 (bearish) to +1 (bullish)
    // -- Pattern Sequence & Divergence ----------------------------------
    int    consecSameDir;         // Consecutive bars same direction as current (0-10)
    bool   volumeExpanding;       // Volume increasing over last 3 bars
    bool   volumeContracting;     // Volume decreasing over last 3 bars
    bool   priceVolDivergence;    // Price up + volume down (or vice versa) = weakness
    bool   hiddenBullDivergence;  // Price HL, RSI lower (uptrend continuation signal)
    bool   hiddenBearDivergence;  // Price LH, RSI higher (downtrend continuation signal)
    bool   regularBullDivergence; // Price LL, RSI higher (reversal warning, oversold)
    bool   regularBearDivergence; // Price HH, RSI lower (reversal warning, overbought)
    bool   tweazerBottom;         // Two candles with matching lows = reversal at support
    bool   tweazerTop;            // Two candles with matching highs = reversal at resistance
    bool   compressingRange;      // Last 5-bar range < 60% of 20-bar range (coiling)
    double seqContinuationScore;  // Composite -1 to +1: positive = continuation likely
    double seqReversalScore;      // Composite -1 to +1: positive = reversal likely
    double probablePathScore;     // Final −20 to +20 added directly to unified score
    
    // SWING DNA -- Sequential market structure (populated by BuildSwingDNA)
    // Encoding: 0=HH  1=HL  2=LH  3=LL  (Higher/Lower High/Low)
    int  swingDNA[10];             // Last N swing types oldest->newest
    int  swingDNALen;              // Valid entries in swingDNA[]
    int  consecutiveHHHL;          // Consecutive HH/HL from most recent
    int  consecutiveLLLH;          // Consecutive LL/LH from most recent
    double swingAmplitudeSlope;    // ATR-normalized slope of swing amplitudes
    bool chochBullishDNA;          // LL->HL->HH sequence = confirmed bullish CHoCH
    bool chochBearishDNA;          // HH->LH->LL sequence = confirmed bearish CHoCH
    bool trendWeakeningBullish;    // HH then LH = uptrend structural crack
    bool trendWeakeningBearish;    // LL then HL = downtrend structural crack
    double keyResistance;          // Densest cluster of recent swing highs (real price)
    double keySupport;             // Densest cluster of recent swing lows (real price)
    double distToResistanceATR;    // ATR-normalized distance to key resistance
    double distToSupportATR;       // ATR-normalized distance to key support
    int    resistanceTouchCount;   // Swing highs clustering at resistance level
    int    supportTouchCount;      // Swing lows clustering at support level
    double srStrength;             // Composite SR level quality 0=weak 1=strong

    // -- Price angle fields (ATR-normalised, in degrees) ------------------
    // Angle = atan(price_change / (ATR x bars)) x (180/π)
    // 0° = flat, 45° = 1 ATR/bar (strong), >65° = blow-off risk
    double ema8Angle;          // Short-term momentum angle (8-bar EMA slope)
    double ema21Angle;         // Medium-term direction angle (21-bar EMA slope)
    double priceAngle14;       // 14-bar linear regression slope angle
    double angleSustainability;// 0-1: how close to the optimal 30-45° range
    double angleRateOfChange;  // Positive=accelerating, negative=decelerating
    bool   angleBlowOff;       // True when angle > 65° (parabolic risk zone)
    bool   angleFlatZone;      // True when angle < 15° (directionless)

    // -- Wave angle DNA — sequence of swing segment angles ------------─
    // Each entry = angle (degrees) of one completed swing wave segment
    // Oldest→newest: waveAngleDNA[0] is oldest, [waveAngleDNALen-1] is most recent
    // This captures Image 1 logic: 45°→27°→62° progression across waves
    double waveAngleDNA[8];    // angles of last 8 swing segments (ATR-normalised, degrees)
    int    waveAngleDNALen;    // valid entries
    double angleMomentum;      // slope of the angle sequence (+ = steepening, - = flattening)
    double angleCumulDelta;    // total angle change across all waves (steepness trajectory)
    bool   angleAccelerating;  // last 2 waves: angle rising >8°
    bool   angleDecelerating;  // last 2 waves: angle falling >8° (degrading trend)
    bool   angleParabolic;     // single wave jumped >20° above prior (blow-off)
    bool   angleRecovery;      // pullback wave shallower than primary + next resuming
    double waveAngleMedian;    // median angle across all stored waves (baseline)
    // -- Advanced S/R context fields ------------------------------------─
    bool   inPremiumZone;          // Upper 50% of key S/R range — prefer selling
    bool   inDiscountZone;         // Lower 50% of key S/R range — prefer buying
    int    srPriceZone;            // 0=discount 1=neutral 2=premium (relative to S/R frame)
    bool   supportRoleReversal;    // Former resistance now tested as support (strong)
    bool   resistanceRoleReversal; // Former support now tested as resistance (strong)
    double srZoneQuality;          // 0-100: touches x recency x H4 confluence x volume
    double levelFreshness;         // 0-1: how recently the nearest level was tested
    double h4SRProximity;          // ATR-normalized distance to nearest H4 swing level
    bool   h4SRConfluence;         // H4 level within ATRx0.8 of current-TF level
    double srTightCluster;         // ATRx0.5 cluster count (institutional precision zone)
    
    // CANDLE ANATOMY -- full dissection of candle character
    // Every candle tells a story about who won the battle that bar.
    // These fields make that story quantifiable and tradeable.

    // Body geometry
    double candleBody;          // Absolute body size in price
    double candleBodyPct;       // Body as % of total range (0-1)  >0.6 = conviction candle
    double upperWickPct;        // Upper wick as % of total range  >0.4 = seller rejection
    double lowerWickPct;        // Lower wick as % of total range  >0.4 = buyer rejection
    double upperWickToBody;     // Upper wick / body ratio  >2.0 = shooting star territory
    double lowerWickToBody;     // Lower wick / body ratio  >2.0 = hammer territory
    bool isBullishCandle;       // Close > Open
    bool isBearishCandle;       // Close < Open

    // Wick pressure scores (directional conviction)
    // Positive = bullish pressure, Negative = bearish pressure
    double wickPressureScore;   // Net wick story: lower wick dominance = bulls absorbing
    double closingStrength;     // Where did price close in the bar's range? 1=top, 0=bottom
                                // >0.7 = strong bullish close, <0.3 = strong bearish close

    // Candle classification (categorical)
    bool isConvictionCandle;    // Large body (>0.6 range), directional close
    bool isIndecisionCandle;    // Doji / near-doji: body < 15% of range
    bool isRejectionCandle;     // Either wick > 2x body (hammer or shooting star)
    bool isBullishRejection;    // Long lower wick, close in upper half (buyers won)
    bool isBearishRejection;    // Long upper wick, close in lower half (sellers won)
    bool isBullishEngulf;       // This candle's body fully engulfs previous bearish candle
    bool isBearishEngulf;       // This candle's body fully engulfs previous bullish candle
    bool isBullishKicker;       // Gap-up open, no overlap with previous bearish bar
    bool isBearishKicker;       // Gap-down open, no overlap with previous bullish bar
    bool isInsideBar;           // Fully contained within previous candle's range
    bool isOutsideBar;          // High > prev high AND Low < prev low (volatile indecision)
    bool isMorningStar;         // 3-bar: bearish + indecision + bullish (reversal)
    bool isEveningStar;         // 3-bar: bullish + indecision + bearish (reversal)
    bool isThreeWhiteSoldiers;  // 3 consecutive bullish conviction candles
    bool isThreeBlackCrows;     // 3 consecutive bearish conviction candles
    // ## Precision enhancement fields ########################################
    double atrPercentile;       // 0-1: where current ATR sits in 50-bar distribution
    double volumeDelta;         // tick volume vs 5-bar avg  (>1.0 = accelerating)
    double priceAcceleration;   // change in price velocity over last 3 bars
    double closePosition;       // close within bar range: 0.0=at low, 1.0=at high
    double barRelativeSize;     // current bar height / 20-bar avg height
    double volExpansion;        // ATR(0) / ATR_avg(20) -- volatility expansion ratio
    double ema200Distance;      // (price ? EMA200) / ATR -- structural trend context
    double bodyRatio;           // body size / total range (0=pure wick, 1=pure body)
    double upperWickRatio;      // upper wick / total range
    double lowerWickRatio;      // lower wick / total range

    // Drama score -- how extreme was this bar?
    // Combines size relative to ATR, wick character, and velocity
    double barDrama;            // 0.0 = boring flat bar, 1.0 = massive explosive candle
                                // Used to weight signal confidence -- dramatic bars in
                                // the right direction are far stronger than quiet ones

    // Sequence context (last 5 bars painted together)
    double momentumBias5;       // Net bias of last 5 candles: +1 all bull, -1 all bear
    double wickBias5;           // Net wick pressure over last 5 bars
    int consecutiveBull;        // Consecutive bullish closes ending at this bar
    int consecutiveBear;        // Consecutive bearish closes ending at this bar

    // Identification
    datetime timestamp;
    int barIndex;

    // -- INTELLIGENCE LAYER 9: ORDER FLOW PROXY --------------------------─
    // Approximate institutional order flow from bar anatomy x tick volume.
    // Cannot get real order flow in MT4, but these 5 signals are the closest
    // observable approximation of buying/selling pressure.
    double buyingPressure;       // Close position in range x volume (0-1 = pure selling, 1 = pure buying)
    double sellingPressure;      // Inverse of buyingPressure
    double pressureDelta;        // Net: buyingPressure - sellingPressure (-1 to +1)
    double pressureDeltaMA;      // 5-bar EMA of pressureDelta (smoothed institutional bias)
    bool   pressureDivergence;   // Price direction ≠ pressure direction (early reversal signal)
    bool   pressureConviction;   // pressureDelta > 0.3 in same direction as signal (confirms)
    double spreadAbsorption;     // When spread contracts during high volume = large player absorption
    bool   liquiditySweep;       // Wick beyond recent high/low with close back inside (stop hunt detected)
    double sweepStrength;        // How far the sweep went x volume (0-1)

    // -- INTELLIGENCE LAYER 10: TRAP DETECTION ----------------------------
    // False breakouts are the #1 cause of losing trades. Detect them before entry.
    bool   bullTrap;             // Broke above resistance, closed back below (short trap)
    bool   bearTrap;             // Broke below support, closed back above (long trap)
    double trapStrength;         // How significant the trap was (0-1)
    bool   nearTrapLevel;        // Within 1 ATR of a recently-trapped level (high-probability reversal)

    // -- INTELLIGENCE LAYER 11: MTF MOMENTUM CONVERGENCE ----------------─
    // Not just EMA alignment but actual momentum agreement: M15, H1, H4 all
    // showing the same momentum direction simultaneously.
    double mtfMomentumScore;     // -3 to +3: each TF adds ±1 if MACD + RSI agree directionally
    bool   mtfFullConvergence;   // All three TFs agree on momentum direction
    bool   mtfDivergence;        // Higher TF momentum opposes lower TF (danger signal)
    double mtfConvictionBonus;   // Direct score add-on when all 3 TFs fully aligned (+0 to +8)

    // -- INTELLIGENCE LAYER 12: BAYESIAN REGIME BELIEF --------------------
    // A probability distribution across all 9 regime states.
    // Concentrated belief = high-conviction trade. Diffuse = reduce size.
    double regimeBelief[9];      // P(regime=i | current evidence): sums to ~1.0
    double beliefEntropy;        // Shannon entropy of belief (0=certain, high=uncertain)
    double beliefConviction;     // 1 - normalised entropy: 0=lost, 1=certain
    int    dominantBeliefRegime; // argmax of regimeBelief[]
    double dominantBeliefProb;   // max(regimeBelief): how confident about the dominant regime

    // -- INTELLIGENCE LAYER 13: INSTITUTIONAL LEVEL MEMORY ----------------
    // Weighted map of price levels that have historically mattered on this instrument.
    double nearestMemoryLevel;   // Closest historically significant level to current price
    double memoryLevelScore;     // Strength of that level (0-100)
    bool   approachingResistance;// Moving toward a strong memory resistance level
    bool   approachingSupport;   // Moving toward a strong memory support level
    double memoryBias;           // Net directional bias from all nearby levels (-1 to +1)
    bool   atHighProbLevel;      // At or within 0.3 ATR of a score-80+ memory level

    // -- INTELLIGENCE LAYER 14: WAVE PHASE CLASSIFICATION ----------------─
    // WHERE in the wave structure are we right now?
    // This is the timing intelligence — same setup, different phase = different expectation.
    int    wavePhase;            // 0=unknown 1=impulse_start 2=impulse_peak 3=correction 4=new_impulse
    double wavePhaseScore;       // Signal multiplier for this wave phase (-1.0 to +1.0)
    bool   optimalEntryWindow;   // True at wave phase 1 and 4 (best timing)
    bool   exhaustionWarning;    // True at wave phase 2 (late in the move)
    double waveMaturity;         // 0=fresh 1=mature: how far into this wave are we?
};

enum AlignmentStatus {
    ALIGNMENT_GOOD,              // Accuracy within 5%, proceed immediately
    ALIGNMENT_NEEDS_TUNING,      // Accuracy 5-18% off, quick tune needed
    ALIGNMENT_NEEDS_FULL_RECAL   // Accuracy >18% off, full recalibration
};

