// HARD OFF by default. Completes Keys-3 thesis item 15 ("episode lifecycle... dissipation exit
// wired") -- WARRANT#65/70 already built the state classifier + dwell measurement, both left
// uncalled by any live decision. When ON, an open trade is closed if the market's readability
// episode (Keys3_EpisodeState) has transitioned to DISSIPATING -- the thesis's own rationale: a
// dissipating episode is exactly the condition under which whatever edge justified the entry is
// breaking down. Cost-audited: Keys3_Readability() is expensive (Hurst+VR+permutation-entropy per
// call, per WARRANT#70's own caution) so the underlying check is cached per-bar (see
// ShouldExitOnDissipation's static Time[0] guard, same idiom used elsewhere in this file, e.g.
// g_PatternState.lastBarTime) -- NOT recomputed per open trade per tick.
// WARRANT#90 (2026-07-22): activated per Manuel's go-ahead.
input bool EnableDissipationExit = true;

